gurmukhi: ਤੳੁ ੲੇ ਰਾਮ ਸਹਿਤ ਜੀਅੈ ਕਹਯੋ ਸੀਅਾ ਤਿਹ ਠੳੁਰ ॥੮੨੩॥
transliteration: Tau E Raam Sahit Jeeai Kahyo Seeaa Tih Thaur||823||
translation: Then at this time all the dead alogwith Ram may be reanimated.823.

gurmukhi: ਸਭੈ ਜਾਗੇ ॥ ਭ੍ਰਮੰ ਭਾਗੇ ॥ ਹਠੰ ਤਯਾਗੇ ॥ ਪਗੰ ਲਾਗੇ ॥੮੨੪॥
transliteration: Sabhai Jaage|| Bhramannd Bhaage|| Hathan Tyaage|| Pagadg Laage||724||
translation: All the dead were reanimated, the illusion of all was removed and all leaving their persistence fell at the feet of SIta.824.

gurmukhi: ਸੀਅਾ ਅਾਨੀ ॥ ਜਗੰ ਰਾਨੀ ॥ ਧਰਮ ਧਾਨੀ ॥ ਸਤੀ ਮਾਨੀ ॥੮੨੫॥
transliteration: Seeaa Aanee|| Jagadg Raanee|| Dharam Dhaanee|| Satimaanee||825||
translation: Sita was accepted as queen of the world and a sati, the source of Dharma.825.

gurmukhi: ਮਨੰ ਭਾੲੀ ॥ ੳੁਰੰ ਲਾੲੀ ॥ ਸਤੀ ਜਾਨੀ ॥ ਮਨੈ ਮਾਨੀ ॥੮੨੬॥
transliteration: Manan Bhaaee|| Uran Laaee|| Satijaanee|| Manai Maanee||826||
translation: Ram loved her and considering her a sati, he hugged her to his bosom.826.

gurmukhi: ਬਹੁਬਿਧਿ ਸੀਅਹਿ ਸਮੋਧ ਕਰ ਚਲੇ ਅਜੁਧਿਅਾ ਦੇਸ ॥ ਲਵ ਕੁਸ ਦੋੳੂ ਪੁਤ੍ਰਨਿ ਸਹਿਤ ਸ੍ਰੀ ਰਘੁਬੀਰ ਨਰੇਸ ॥੮੨੭॥
transliteration: Bahoubidh(i) Seeah(i) Samodh Kar Chale Ajudhiaa Des|| Lav Kous Dooo Poutran(i) Sahit Sriraghoubeer Dares||827||
translation: Instructing Sita in many ways and taking Lava and Kusha with him Raghuvir Ram started for Ajodhya.827.

gurmukhi: ਬਹੁਤੁ ਭਾਂਤਿ ਕਰ ਸਿਸਨ ਸਮੋਧਾ ॥ ਸੀਯ ਰਘੁਬੀਰ ਚਲੇ ਪੁਰ ਅੳੁਧਾ ॥
transliteration: Bahout(u) Bhaant(i) Kar Sisan Samodhaa|| Seeya Raghoubeer Chale Pur Audhaa||
translation: The children were also instructed in many ways and Sita and ram moved towards Oudh.

gurmukhi: ਅਨਿਕ ਬੇਖ ਸੇ ਸਸਤ੍ਰ ਸੁਹਾੲੇ ॥ ਜਾਨਤ ਤੀਨ ਰਾਮ ਬਨ ਅਾੲੇ ॥੮੨੮॥
transliteration: Anik Bekh Se Sastra Suhaae|| Jaanat Teen Raam Ban Aae||828||
translation: All the there were carrying weapons in different styles and it seemed that three Rams were walking.828.

gurmukhi: ੲਿਤਿ ਸ੍ਰੀ ਬਚਿਤ੍ਰ ਨਾਟਕੇ ਰਾਮਵਤਾਰੇ ਤਿਹੂ ਭਿਰਾਤਨ ਸੈਨਾ ਸਹਿਤ ਜੀਬੋ ॥
transliteration: It(i) Sribachitra Naatake Raamavdare Tihoo Bhiraatan Sainaa Sahit Jiho||
translation: End of the Chapter entitled The Reanimation of the Three Brothers alongwith their forces in Ramavtar in BACHITTAR NATAK.

gurmukhi: ਸੀਤਾ ਦੁਹੂ ਪੁਤ੍ਰਨ ਸਹਿਤ ਪੁਰੀ ਅਵਧ ਪ੍ਵੇਸ ਕਥਨੰ ॥
transliteration: Seetaa Duhoo Poutran Sahit Poutiavadh Praves Kathanan||
translation: The description of the Entry of Sita alongwith her two sons in Oudhpuri :
